headers.subject: [tosdr:2548] Instagram may transfer personal info to a country with different data protection laws

html:
• Instagram, its Affiliates, or Service Providers may transfer information that we collect about you, including personal information across borders and from your country or jurisdiction to other countries or jurisdictions around the world. If you are located in the European Union or other regions with laws governing data collection and use that may differ from U.S. law, please note that we may transfer information, including personal information, to a country and jurisdiction that does not have the same data protection laws as your jurisdiction.
http://instagram.com/about/legal/privacy/

Title: Instagram may transfer your personal information to a country with different data protection laws

Topic: personal-data

Summary: When handling your personal information, Instagram may transfer that information to a country or jurisdiction with data protection laws that differ from the jurisdiction where you reside. This means that it's possible they may transfer information to a country with less stringent data protection laws than the country you currently live in.

Score: 50 (mediocre)
